# Baseline — its OWN database (ADR 0038: one database per product).
#
# Each product owns its own DATABASE_URL; there is no shared DB and no
# cross-product foreign keys. Baseline does NOT read BBL's lineage DB.
# Copy this file to `.env` (gitignored) for local dev.
#
# Local dev = Postgres.app. The RUNTIME client (libpq/pg) defaults the user to
# your macOS username, so it can be omitted — BUT Prisma Migrate's engine does
# NOT default it and errors P1010 without one. Set the explicit user for local
# dev, e.g. postgresql://YOURUSER@localhost:5432/baseline_dev.
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://localhost:5432/baseline_dev"

# --- Auth (Better Auth — per-product identity, ADR 0038 D5) -------------------
# Baseline carries its OWN Better Auth instance (no shared identity with BBL or
# Mammoth). Email+password only — Baseline has no transactional-email infra, so
# no magic-link/social. Copy this file to `.env` and generate a real secret.
#
# Required. Generate a strong random secret (e.g. `openssl rand -base64 32`).
# NEVER commit a real value — set it in `.env` locally and on the Vercel project.
BETTER_AUTH_SECRET="generate-a-strong-random-secret"
# The canonical origin Better Auth signs/validates against. On Vercel previews it
# falls back to VERCEL_URL automatically; set the explicit prod URL on deploy.
BETTER_AUTH_URL="http://localhost:3100"
